Overview of phonology, basic concepts of phonetics, English sounds and their formation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1) improve the students' pronunciation ; 2) acquire the rhythm and intonation of the language; 3) to teach phonetic transcription; 4) to teach to compare the phonetic and phonological systems of English-Estonian / Russian languages.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course, the student: 1) knows the basic concepts of phonetics; 2) Is familiar with English vowels, combinations of vowels and the ways in which they are formed and is aware of the differences and similarities between English and Estonian / Russian pronunciation; 3) has acquired correct pronunciation of English; 4) has acquired the rhythm and intonation of the English language; 5) can do phonetic transcription of text; 6) knows and is able to use various techniques to correct possible interference errors.
